tephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":1,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Luvetoft was born in 1336, in Yorkshire, England as the daughter of William de Luvetot. She married Edward Furnival about 1356, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1380, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1336–Abt 1380":"1336–umbes 1380","1336–1380":"1336–1380","1330–1383":"1330–1383","1356–1443":"1356–1443","1305–Male":"1305–Surnud","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1356":"1356","1443":"1443","1453":"1453","about 1356":"umbes 1356","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","Abt 1380":"umbes 1380","1380":"1380","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1336–Abt 1380":"1336–noin 1380","1336–1380":"1336–1380","1330–1383":"1330–1383","1356–1443":"1356–1443","1305–Male":"1305–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1336":"1336","1356":"1356","1443":"1443","1453":"1453","about 1356":"noin 1356","1330":"1330","1383":"1383","Abt 1380":"noin 1380","1380":"1380","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England","England":"England","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuni